<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4904] Python TSocket read() and write() allow low level exceptions to escape</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4904</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The calls to socket send() and recv() inside write() and read() were allowing exceptions to escape:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;OSError&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;socket.error&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ssl.Error&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;These need to be captured and translated to an appropriate TTransportException.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
